1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
AI infrastructure is becoming more powerful, expensive, and concentrated.
What if people could participate in it, not only consume it?

2
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:28,000
GridOne is a collaborative compute network.
Only verified work earns transparent prototype AI Credits.

3
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Builder control comes first. Smart Contribution protects foreground activity,
and the prototype accepts only an allow-listed task using public or synthetic data.

4
00:00:43,000 --> 00:01:10,000
The coordinator splits one document-vector job into eight microtasks
and leases them to two isolated workers.

5
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Berlin deliberately tampers with its first answer.
GridOne rejects the mismatch and safely requeues the task.

6
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Only verified tasks create credits, and every balance change links to a receipt.
Build Week credits are simulated and non-redeemable.

7
00:01:49,000 --> 00:02:13,000
Codex and GPT-5.6 helped pressure-test the idea, design the protocol,
implement the dashboard and verification logic, and write the automated tests.

8
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:28,000
GridOne demonstrates a community-powered layer for verifiable AI work.
Don't just use AI. Help build it.

